'''Amerikis Square''' ({{lang-el|Πλατεία Αμερικής}}, ''Plateia Amerikis'', "America Square") is located in central [[Athens]], [[Greece]]. It is an open area adjacently to [[Patision Street]], on the western borders of [[Kypseli, Athens|Kypseli]]. Formerly called Agamon Square, literally "square ''of the unmarried''", the neighbourhood around the square includes, along with central Kypseli, many modernist apartment buildings built during the 1930s.<ref>{{el icon}} Chara Tzanavara (18 October 2009), [http://www.enet.gr/?i=news.el.article&id=92725 Στα ίχνη του μοντερνισμού], ''[[Eleftherotypia]]''. Retrieved 18 February 2017.</ref>

