'''Claude Champy''' (b. September 12, 1944<ref>{{cite web|url=http://galerie-capazza.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=109:claude-champy&layout=default&lang=en|title=Biography of Claude Champy, ceramics|author=marc|date=|work=galerie-capazza.com|accessdate=22 January 2016}}</ref>) is a French [[ceramist]].
In 1988, he received the Grand Prix of the [[Suntory Museum of Art]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lacostegallery.com/dynamic/artist.asp?artistid=244 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-01-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160128202958/http://www.lacostegallery.com/dynamic/artist.asp?artistid=244 |archivedate=2016-01-28 |df= }}</ref> At that time he formed links with Japanese ceramists and also created [[Raku ware]].
His works are part of the [[Charles-Adrien Buéno's collection]].
