[[Image:Czech_iguanodontid_fossil.JPG|thumb|''[[Burianosaurus]]'' femur, found in 2003 near Mezholezy.]]

'''Peruc-Korycany Formation''' is a [[Geology|geologic]] unit of Upper [[Cretaceous]] age, located mostly in the [[Czech Republic]]. [[Dinosaur]] fossil remains about 94 million years old ([[Cenomanian]] stage) were found in 2003 near the village Mezholezy ([[Miskovice]]), by [[Kutná Hora]]. This small ornithopod dinosaur was officially named as ''[[Burianosaurus]] augustai'' in 2017.

