'''Soweto TV''' is a [[South African]] community television channel broadcasting in the biggest township in South Africa, [[Soweto]]. The channel is free-to-air in [[Gauteng Province]] and it also broadcast to South African subscribers on the [[DStv]] pay TV service on channel 251. 
The channel studios are situated on one of the most popular streets in Soweto, [[Vilakazi Street]]; well known for being the only street in the world to have the historical residences of two [[Nobel Prize]] winners, namely [[Nelson Mandela]] and [[Archbishop Desmond Tutu]].
Soweto TV programming is mostly Sowetan content as per [[ICASA's]] regulations of over 60% local content.

